snippet.description:
A tribute to Ronnie James Dio...Official lyrics for the song

Notice (12/9/2014): I don't know whether Dio died at the age of 65, 66, 67 or 84, the first thing you notice when you open the video is this and I am pretty sure that everyone gets tempted and want to correct me by saying "He didn't die at the age of 65, he died___" etc etc. but guess what! It actually doesn't matter a lot, does it? Master Dio is not with us anymore, let's all stop giving a shit about my mistake since I was misled by something I had read on Facebook back in 2010 and enjoy this amazing song. I really love you all for giving me and Dio all these views and I also enjoy reading comments from people trying to explain the meaning of the song. Each one of you has something special to say about this song, calling it "precious" or "symbolic" or even "a song about someone coming out of the closet" (lol, yeah, people have said that here) and reading the comments sometimes is fun! But about that age-thing...Seriously, stop wasting seconds of your life correcting me, it was just a mistake. Wherever you are, I wish you prosperity

Notice (14/4/2015): For some weird reason, WMG decided to block this video and for some days I was unable to watch it ("lol dumbass, it was blocked, of course you weren't able to watch it"). But now that I opened my video manager page, I saw that everything is ok. I don't know how many days have passed since they unblocked it, I actually have no idea what's wrong with the whole copyright thing. This video is a dedication, the least i could do of course, to one of my favourite musicians and it serves promotional uses. All rights go to the respective artist and record label, don't worry, I buy your stuff damn it. Aaaanyway, I hope y'all boyz and girlz out there are able to watch it and sing along with me. Cheers, I hope no label will bother me in the near future about it :D
snippet.title: Dio-Rainbow In The Dark (lyrics)

Rime of the Ancient Mariner - Iron Maiden

"Day after day, day after day,
we stuck nor breath nor motion

all the boards did shrink

there comes a ship over the line

in her sails and no tide.

each turned his face with a ghastly pang,

Now the curse is finally lifted

And then a boat came sailing towards him

And the ship sinks like lead into the sea
And the hermit shrieves the Mariner of his sins.

The Mariner's bound to tell of his story

If you want more Beatles' videos with lyrics just leave a comment below ^.^
sorry for the little delay of the lyrics at one part which is nearly at the end.
Enjoy :))))

Lyrics:


Picture yourself in a boat on a river,
With tangerine trees and marmalade skies.
Somebody calls you, you answer quite slowly,
A girl with kaleidoscope eyes.

Cellophane flowers of yellow and green,
Towering over your head.
Look for the girl with the sun in her eyes,
And she's gone.

Lucy in the sky with diamonds,
Lucy in the sky with diamonds,
Lucy in the sky with diamonds,
Ah... Ah...

Follow her down to a bridge by a fountain,
Where rocking horse people eat marshmallow pies.
Everyone smiles as you drift past the flowers,
That grow so incredibly high.

Newspaper taxis appear on the shore,
Waiting to take you away.
Climb in the back with your head in the clouds,
And you're gone.

Picture yourself on a train in a station,
With plasticine porters with looking glass ties.
Suddenly someone is there at the turnstile,
The girl with kaleidoscope eyes.
snippet.title: Lucy In The Sky With Diamonds - The Beatles (lyrics)

snippet.description:
Welcome to Lynyrd Skynyrd - Free Bird w/ lyrics! A very popular song, it's old but gold! One of my personal favorites!

NOTE: If you DON'T like the annotations, then TURN them off! It's not difficult. Please refrain from telling everyone you did so, honestly no one cares here. Just listen for the song! 

- Feel free to rock out loud or do air guitar. :) Yes, I do have duct tape in case you BREAK your air guitar... The struggle is real...

-I made this video about this song with my brother when we shared this YouTube account when we were 15. Obviously, there's multiple misspellings, confusing grammar and odd annotations. I am aware of these, but I'm leaving the annotations in since they remind me of the "simpler" life. :)-

Rock On! \m/ ( ^.^ ) \m/

-All Rights go to Lynyrd Skynyrd. I did not make this song and no copyright was intended.-

Lastly, feel free to check out @ShapingtheSilence !
Link: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCehaxxooGG9kCmR6cdUW2MA
snippet.title: Lynyrd Skynyrd Freebird w/ Lyrics

snippet.description:
Great song

Lyrics
In a white room, with black curtains, near the station.
Blackroof country, no gold pavements, tired starlings.
Silver horses, ran down moonbeams in your dark eyes
Dawnlight smiles on you leaving, my contentment.

I'll wait in this place where the sun never shines
Wait in this place where the shadows run from themselves

You said no strings could secure you at the station
Platform ticket, restless diesels, goodbye windows
I walked into such a sad time at the station
As I walked out, felt my own need just beginning

I'll wait in the queue when the trains come back
Lie with you where the shadows run from themselves

At the party she was kindness in the hard crowd
Consolation for the old wound now forgotten
Yellow tigers crouched in jungles in her dark eyes
She's just dressing, goodbye windows, tired starlings

I'll sleep in this place with the lonely crowd
Lie in the dark where the shadows run from themselves
snippet.title: Cream- White Room
